answerText: Birch reduction[10] Most alkene hydrogenations can be described by this term, which describes additions in the electrophile and nucleophile add from the same side of the plane of a double bond. They are contrasted with "anti" additions.

question: Question: Answer the following about reactions in which hydrogen atoms are added to compounds, for 10 points each: [10] In this reduction, which is done with alkali metals in liquid ammonia, benzene is reduced to a cyclohexadiene. It proceeds by a radical mechanism.
